 was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Violet","meanings":["From the name of the flower (Old French <i>violette</i>, Late Latin <i>violetta</i>, a diminutive of <i>viola</i>). This was one of the earliest flower names to become popular in Britain, being used as early as  1700  and becoming well established in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gautier II d'Enghien seigneur d'Enghien was born about 1267, in Enghien, Hainaut, Belgium, his father, Gauthier I d'Enghien, was 47 and his mother, Marie de Réthel, was 23. He married Yolande de Flandre on 24 July 1287. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1310, in Conversano, Bari, Puglia, Italy, at the age of 44."},"et":{"about 1267–1310":"umbes 1267–1310","1267–1310":"1267–1310","1273–1313":"1273–1313","1295–1378":"1295–1378","1302–1345":"1302–1345","1307–Female":"1307–Surnud","1222–1271":"1222–1271","1245–1316":"1245–1316","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1295":"1295","1273":"1273","1271":"1271","9 May 1271":"9. mai 1271","5 June 1302":"5. juuni 1302","1316":"1316","24 July 1287":"24. juuli 1287","1302":"1302","1313":"1313","1345":"1345","1378":"1378","1245":"1245","1267":"1267","1310":"1310","1222":"1222","about 1267":"umbes 1267","about 1295":"umbes 1295","1307":"1307","Enghien,7850,Hainaut,Wallonie,BELGIQUE,":"Enghien, Hainaut, Belgia","Belgium":"Belgia","of France":"Prantsusmaa","Enghien, Hainaut, Belgium":"Enghien, Hainaut, Belgia","Conversano, Bari, Apulia, Italy":"Conversano, Bari, Puglia, Itaalia"},"fi":{"about 1267–1310":"noin 1267–1310","1267–1310":"1267–1310","1273–1313":"1273–1313","12